I think you’re aiming at something that many founders overlook: you’re not just selling caffeine, you’re trying to create a behavior.

The companies with the strongest repeat purchases often become part of a daily routine:

* Coffee → morning ritual.
* Energy drink → commute/work ritual.
* Gum → after meals.
* Zyn → frequent, repeat behavior.
* Stanley cup → carrying water all day.

Wild Hawg has the opportunity to become:

The “energy chew” ritual.

That changes how you should think about the product.

⸻

Instead of asking…

“How much caffeine should each gummy have?”

Ask:

“What ritual do I want someone to have?”

⸻

