The design implication

Everything should reinforce the ritual.

The pouch

Should open easily with one hand.

The gummies

Shouldn’t stick together.

Texture

Chewy enough to feel satisfying.

Not so tough that they become work.

Flavor

Stay pleasant over multiple pieces.

If someone eats eight or ten over a couple of hours, the flavor shouldn’t become overwhelming or cloying.

⸻

I would actually optimize for this metric:

“Minutes of Enjoyment”

Instead of:

200 mg caffeine

Measure:

How many enjoyable minutes does one pack provide?

If an energy drink gives someone 30–45 minutes of sipping…

Could Wild Hawg give someone 30–60 minutes of enjoyable chewing?

That’s a completely different way to evaluate the product.

